<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-13778] Fetch from follower should never run the preferred read replica selection</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-13778</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The design purpose of the code is that only the leader broker can determine the preferred read-replica.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
readFromLocalLog()
....
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// If we are the leader, determine the preferred read-replica
&lt;/span&gt;val preferredReadReplica = clientMetadata.flatMap(
  metadata =&amp;gt; findPreferredReadReplica(partition, metadata, replicaId, fetchInfo.fetchOffset, fetchTimeMs)) &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But in fact, since the broker does not judge whether it is the leader or not, the follower will also execute the preferred read-replica selection.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
partition.leaderReplicaIdOpt.flatMap { leaderReplicaId =&amp;gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Don&apos;t look up preferred &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; follower fetches via normal replication and
&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (Request.isValidBrokerId(replicaId))
    None
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
